AN ACT relating to governmental entities; requiring certain units of
government of this State to accept certain forms of
payment; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill requires, with certain exceptions, each officer, agency, branch, board,
2 commission, department, division, bureau, district or other unit of government of
3 this State to accept, as payment for any fee, tax or other debt, payment by debit
4 card, credit card, check, money order, electronic transfer of money or cash.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 237 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in paragraph (b) of
4 subsection 1 of NRS 360A.040, each governmental agency shall
5 accept as payment for any fee, tax or other debt to the
6 governmental agency payment by debit card, credit card, check,
7 money order, electronic transfer of money or cash.
8 2. As used in this section:
9 (a) “Electronic transfer of money” has the meaning ascribed
10 to it in NRS 353.1467.
